# Reference for Railway variables (copy values in the Railway dashboard; do not commit secrets).
#
# Production URLs (this deployment)
# ---------------------------------
# Frontend: https://one-yield-production.up.railway.app
# Backend:  https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# Railway variable references: the name inside ${{ ... }} MUST match your service slug
# exactly (Dashboard → service → Settings). Example:
#   VITE_API_URL="${{one-yield-backend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}"
# resolves to a hostname only (no https://) — the app adds https:// automatically.
# Prefer setting explicit URLs in the dashboard to avoid broken builds if a reference fails:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#   VITE_WS_URL=https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# Do NOT set PORT manually on the frontend service — Railway injects it. The container must
# listen on process.env.PORT (this repo uses serve-static.mjs / Dockerfile.serve).
#
# VITE_PUBLIC_URL is not used by this Vite app unless you add it to vite.config; safe to omit.
#
# Backend (one-yield-backend)
# ---------------------------
# PORT is set automatically by Railway — do not hardcode in the service.
# DATABASE_URL: use Railway Postgres plugin reference ${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}
#
# CORS_ORIGIN (required for browser calls from the frontend):
#   https://one-yield-production.up.railway.app,http://localhost:8080
# Use comma-separated origins; include local only if you still dev against prod API.
#
# RPC_URL / FACTORY_ADDRESS / keys: match your Hedera testnet deployment.
#
# Frontend (one-yield-frontend)
# -----------------------------
# VITE_API_URL (no trailing slash):
#   https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# VITE_WS_URL (Socket.IO — same host as API; optional if you rely on VITE_API_URL):
#   https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# If you use Railway references like ${{one-yield-backend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}, ensure the
# resolved value has no trailing slash. Hostname-only also works; the app prepends https://
# (http:// for localhost / 127.0.0.1).
